  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ACCOUNTS EXECUTIVE",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage the full set of accounts for multiple food court and coffee shop outlets,  covering Accounts Receivable (AR), Accounts Payable (AP), General Ledger  (GL), and month-end closing.</li>\n  <li>Prepare  and review monthly financial statements, profit &amp; loss (P&amp;L)  reports, balance sheets, and supporting schedules.</li>\n  <li>Reconcile  daily sales against cash, NETS, credit card, and delivery platform collections.</li>\n  <li>Verify  supplier invoices, staff claims, petty cash, and process vendor payments  in a timely manner.</li>\n  <li>Perform  monthly bank reconciliations and ensure accuracy of financial records.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with accounting standards, company policies, and statutory requirements (e.g., IRAS, GST submissions).</li>\n  <li>Support  annual audit and tax matters, liaising with external auditors, tax agents,  and banks.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with operations and management to monitor costs, profitability, and variances across outlets.</li>\n  <li>Oversee  and participate in stock take audits, ensuring accuracy of inventory  records and proper COGS reporting.</li>\n  <li>Assist in budgeting, cost control, and cash flow management.</li>\n  <li>Perform  ad-hoc duties and financial reports as assigned by management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree  in Accounting, Finance, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum  2–3 years of relevant accounting experience in the F&amp;B industry (food courts, restaurants, coffee shops, or related sectors).</li>\n  <li>Proven  experience in handling full sets of accounts independently.</li>\n  <li>Proficient  in Xero and Microsoft Excel (experience with other accounting software such as SQL, QuickBooks, or MYOB will be an advantage).</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of F&amp;B operations, cost allocations, and inventory/COGS tracking.</li>\n  <li>Meticulous, well-organized, and able to meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Good  communication skills and ability to work with both operations and  management teams.</li>\n  <li>Comfortable  with working at multiple locations (Tanjong Pagar, Katong and Aljunied) as  required</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
